node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

node.text:
HOME TOUR | 8 Yard House
​.
@studio__bright design a private oasis in Melbourne’s North Fitzroy through eight different, integrated outdoor spaces.
​.
​Rather than simply creating a large glazed pavilion to a rear garden, @studio__bright designed a series of outdoor garden rooms, each one thoughtfully aligned to the living areas.
​.
​Read more about @studio__bright's award-winning project on estliving.com – link in profile.
​.
​Design @studio__bright
​Build @basisbuilders
​Styling @jesskneebone
​Landscape @peachy_green_
​Photography @arorygardiner
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/8-yard-house-studio-bright/

node.text:
ARCHITECTURE | Snake River Cabin
​.
@mcleanquinlan designed Snake River Cabin for their clients to recharge and reflect in the spectacular landscape, ​located in Snake River Valley, Eastern Oregon.
​.
Looking out to the mountains beyond, two structures take in the views beyond while ​Douglas Fir wraps each space in an overwhelming sense of warmth.
​.
​Design @mcleanquinlan
​Photography David Agnello 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

node.text:
BEST OF EST | Lake Houses
​.
​We’re revisiting six of our favourite lake houses from the Swedish woods to the rocky outcrops of Canada.
​.
​The Rock by Gort Scott takes its name from its location, built into a rock in Whistler, Canada, as an extension of the natural landscape it inhabits. 
​.
​Perched on a rocky outcrop overlooking Alta Lake, the home resides on a series of landscaped levels cut into the mountainside, surrounded by pine tree forests and mountain ranges.
​.
​​See our full edit of lake houses on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @gortscott
​Photography @arorygardiner
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/best-of-est-lake-houses/

node.text:
KITCHEN COVET | Butler's Pantries 
​.
​Butler’s pantries or sculleries are the unsung heroes of the kitchen. They’re where all of the action takes place out of sight; for entertaining, your morning coffee, concealing clutter (dishes) and providing storage space. 
​.
These utilitarian workspaces are a consistent feature in premium kitchens featured on est. ​Together with @bellingau, we set foot inside some of our favourite examples, where clever design intervention is reflected in the flow and functional details.
​.
See our edit of butler’s pantries and sculleries on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @sandersandking, @pleysierperkins,  @mimdesignstudio, @studioprineas, @carolewhiting, @studiofour.net.au, @arentpykestudio, @luigirosselliarchitects, @chrisrosestylist & @templetonarchitecture 
​Photography @sharyncairns, @chriswarnes, @jacksheltonphoto, @shannonmcgrath7, @prueruscoe, @gemmola & @benhosking1984
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/kitchen-covet-butlers-pantries/

​.
@austin_design_associates make a case for understated and enduring design in their renovation of a family home in Sandringham, Melbourne.

node.text:
HOME TOUR | Bondi House
​.
​“The central courtyard was an early idea we developed to gather light and segment the living level into zones, which we think is more interesting in a small space, rather than that feeling of just being in one long room.”
– Fox Johnston director Conrad Johnston
​.
​Bondi House by @foxjohnston  reveals a blueprint for multi-level living within a compact corner site in Bondi’s leafy back streets.
​.
​Together with @boschhomeau, we learn how this multifaceted family home responds to the challenging site it inhabits through form, function and a deep appreciation for the outdoors. Read more via the link in profile. 
.

Styling @sarahellisonstudio
